The input array `arr` is not null.
The length of the input array `arr` is at least 2.
The input array `arr` is sorted in strictly increasing order.
The first element of the input array `arr` is 1.
All elements of the input array `arr` are prime numbers.
The input integer `k` is greater than or equal to 1.
The input integer `k` is less than or equal to `arr.length * (arr.length - 1) / 2`.
